 StringPart.class.getClassLoader();\n        try (InputStream input = classLoader.getResourceAsStream(STRING_PART_RESOURCE)) {\n            assertThat(input).isNotNull();\n            byte[] classBytes = input.readAllBytes();\n            replaceSyntheticAttributeName(classBytes);\n            return classBytes;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static void replaceSyntheticAttributeName(byte[] classBytes) {\n        int constantPoolCount = unsignedShort(classBytes, 8);\n        int offset = 10;\n        byte[] synthetic = \"Synthetic\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.ISO_8859_1);\n        byte[] replacement = \"Synthetix\".getBytes(StandardCharsets.ISO_8859_1);\n        for (int index = 1; index < constantPoolCount; index++) {\n            int tag = classBytes[offset++] & 0xff;\n            switch (tag) {\n                case 1:\n                    int length = unsignedShort(classBytes, offset);\n                    offset += 2;\n                    if (length == synthetic.length\n                            && startsWith(classBytes, synthetic, offset)) {\n                        System.arraycopy(replacement, 0, classBytes, offset, replacement.length);\n                    }\n                    offset += length;\n                    break;\n                case 3:\n                case 4:\n                case 9:\n                case 10:\n                case 11:\n                case 12:\n                case 18:\n                    offset += 4;\n                    break;\n                case 5:\n                case 6:\n                    offset += 8;\n                    index++;\n                    break;\n                case 7:\n                case 8:\n                case 16:\n                case 19:\n                case 20:\n                    offset += 2;\n                    break;\n                case 15:\n                    offset += 3;\n                    break;\n                default:\n                    throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"Unsupported constant pool tag: \" + tag);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static int unsignedShort(byte[] bytes, int offset) {\n        return ((bytes[offset] & 0xff) << 8) | (bytes[offset + 1] & 0xff);\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] send(StringPart part) throws Exception {"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class StringPartClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        private StringPartClassLoader(URL[] urls, ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(urls, parent);\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                if (STRING_PART_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                    Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                    if (loadedClass == null) {\n                        loadedClass = findClass(name);\n                    }\n                    if (resolve) {\n                        resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                    }\n                    return loadedClass;\n                }\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n        }\n    }", "newText": "    private static final class StringPartClassLoader extends URLClassLoader {\n        private final byte[] stringPartClassBytes;\n\n        private StringPartClassLoader(\n                URL[] urls,\n                ClassLoader parent,\n                byte[] stringPartClassBytes) {\n            super(urls, parent);\n            this.stringPartClassBytes = stringPartClassBytes;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Class<?> loadClass(String name, boolean resolve) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            synchronized (getClassLoadingLock(name)) {\n                if (STRING_PART_CLASS_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                    Class<?> loadedClass = findLoadedClass(name);\n                    if (loadedClass == null) {\n                        loadedClass = loadStringPartClass(name);\n                    }\n                    if (resolve) {\n                        resolveClass(loadedClass);\n                    }\n                    return loadedClass;\n                }\n                return super.loadClass(name, resolve);\n            }\n        }\n\n        private Class<?> loadStringPartClass(String name) throws ClassNotFoundException {\n            if (stringPartClassBytes == null) {\n                return findClass(name);\n            }\n            return defineClass(name, stringPartClassBytes, 0, stringPartClassBytes.length);\n        }\n    }"}]}
[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering class transformation techniques**\n\nI'm thinking about the method being package-private static synthetic. We might be able to manually transform the class file byte array, but using dynamic class loading for a duplicate library class seems excessive. Do I need reflection for testing coverage? The public API doesn't require it, but an existing class does. Direct bytecode transformations might feel hacky and not very idiomatic. If needed, I could create a subclass with the specified source file and line under the appropriate package.\n\n**Analyzing classloader behavior**\n\nI'm considering how the `defineClass` function in the same package as the parent's `PartBase` but under a different classloader could function. It seems like it attempts a static initialization of `LogFactory`, which might just work. I'm curious about if this setup will lead to any issues related to loading or referencing elements from the parent. I'll need to keep an eye on compatibility and initialization order as I explore this further!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_010dd087628ce544016a04aaab6628819f9ca1f8a18e3b479a\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqBKr0sonQwMDy2AvC8HHyXopieM5ipgsAUHH5OotD1GHpCF74eCNfeHWfWtrwc8IiMZfh5FywWOQlkRV-DgOdFZkUoJYmwBAp7HZoXCYZLJosiqyiWV7BMhx4nyPHDNxTF_i3O51cAeZO7MNtzMgiA7p7PZajjjDQiBeXTECJYPkweWf5OCChB4nrrC28u-HAe0zJFTf13zN-xKZb6R_adx6k2Plin3n9SEQVMDoG3Uy7PuzjoqTsL979NGLPC-xOisBiPi9LH0IQIydO9o_j4K27fBmWsr4XaWeGrdAgdhT3-BtzFbPUZr6gT6S39IIkVnEWvaTKhCu4UZKDsxRsI1dlLVHCQSVgUC1-xjfVrfSHMj4VXFJd0oZd-RLPNk4Udatfx6sgQD2rt9V_B-hks12KNtoRE_jAwatR_9VE6Am_cGJHSZzePe9rC25_KpQHZRSjOl3eZC4LeVg5F2coo-DK2S3CaPoww4Y-C7po0GywN1PLO6udWZLtmHHeTezU3B1AHAdxMkT8mQyvColu2HxOydRiAKBwjfwBg81vCLIv5-sEAZJC8QTt0WOytBinWsNXU8Dsa1KXwlBsGguam1RZ9P_z9p73aow_sODYQEV3ed1ZM2oqXXH9oyCq7QA4kjnDEOAUa9ZgeWrNa74NvqognMhCf47Vh90FWUXE9xGF1-BtmZJxVE1-Lz7DQNTfBSN